        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "HackerEarth is a Bengaluru-founded technical assessment and developer community platform. It serves 3,000+ companies globally and hosts a developer network of 10 million+ users. It is known for its large coding challenge library (40,000+ problems across 1,000+ skills), hackathon hosting, and AI-powered interview tooling."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does AssessIQ differ from HackerEarth for structured B2B hiring?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "HackerEarth combines a public developer community with its enterprise hiring tools — meaning it benefits companies that want to tap community talent or run high-profile hackathons. AssessIQ is a pure B2B platform with no public leaderboards or developer profiles. Its focus is structured, auditable selection: anchor-based rubrics, scoring bands, per-answer rationale, and full attempt logs. For companies that need defensible hiring decisions with a clear scoring rationale, AssessIQ's structured approach is purpose-built for that use case."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does HackerEarth support proctoring for assessments?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "HackerEarth includes anti-cheating tools such as Smart Browser, copy/paste detection, and AI-generated code tracking as part of its assessment platform. AssessIQ's proctoring includes browser tab-switch detection, full-screen enforcement, webcam monitoring with anomaly flagging, copy-paste restriction, and a timestamped event log per attempt that admins can review. Both platforms address proctoring; the depth and auditability of proctoring logs differs — evaluate against your compliance requirements."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is HackerEarth good for hackathon-based hiring in India?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "HackerEarth is a strong choice if hackathon-based talent discovery is a priority — it hosts a global developer community and supports virtual, in-person, and hybrid hackathons with full logistics management. AssessIQ is not a hackathon platform; it is designed for structured pre-employment screening and institutional exams, not community-driven events."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which platform has a larger coding challenge library?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "HackerEarth publicly states a library of 40,000+ coding problems across 1,000+ skills and 40+ programming languages. AssessIQ's coding question packs are curated specifically for Indian IT hiring role stacks — focused on Python, Java, SQL, React, .NET, and related technologies — with calibration for Indian candidate pools. If breadth of coding problems across many languages is the priority, HackerEarth has more volume. If curated packs calibrated for Indian IT hiring are the priority, AssessIQ is built for that."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I try AssessIQ for free?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. AssessIQ has a free starting point — create an account and run assessments without a credit card. This lets you evaluate AssessIQ against your real hiring workflow before deciding."
      }
    }
  ]
};

